    "difficulty": 4,
    "stem": "$a:b = 2:3$ and $b:c = 4:5$. What is $a:c$?",
    "options": [
      { "id": "A", "text": "2:5" },
      { "id": "B", "text": "6:15" },
      { "id": "C", "text": "8:15" },
      { "id": "D", "text": "2:3" },
      { "id": "E", "text": "1:2" }
    ],
    "answer": "C",
    "solutionStandard": "Scale both ratios to share the same $b$: $a:b = 2:3 = 8:12$, and $b:c = 4:5 = 12:15$. So $a:b:c = 8:12:15$, giving $a:c = 8:15$.",
